	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm sorry, my sk friend.. a previous reply to this post was entirely accurate.. if your HT is coming up only when you die, then you die too much and too quickly.. it take 90 minutes (1 EQ day) for HT to reload.. no more, no less.. now, as far as using your HT.. i find that i very rarely ever use my HT to "save the day".. while at the lower lvls it will do a significant amount of damage to the mob, at the higher lvls it won't take off enough to make a healthy mob start running.. for this reason, i suggest the following.. if you feel comfortable with being an sk and feel that you can handle yourself in battle without having to rely on this HT safety net, do what i do.. use it everytime it pops up on whatever mob you are facing.. just use it like a wizard would use a dd, strictly for damage-dealing purposes.. or, in the case that you are camping a rare spawn, maybe save it for when that rare spawn pops up, so you can ensure that it will go down quickly and keep your group relatively safe.. if you're like me, you'll find that having HT in available for weeks on end is hardly a necessary safety net..<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
